    int[] intArray = ArrayUtils.toPrimitive(myList.toArray(new Integer[myList.size()]));

This way you don&#39;t reinvent the wheel.  Commons Lang has a great many useful things that Java left out.  Above, I chose to create an Integer list of the right size.  You can also use a 0-length static Integer array and let Java allocate an array of the right size:

    static final Integer[] NO_INTS = new Integer[0];
       ....
    int[] intArray2 = ArrayUtils.toPrimitive(myList.toArray(NO_INTS));

[1]: http://commons.apache.org/lang
