I just recently, after seven long years with Maven, learned about toolchains.xml. Maven has it even documented and supports it from 2.0.9 - [toolchains documentation][1] 

So I added a toolchains.xml file to my ~/.m2/ folder with following content:

&lt;!-- begin snippet: xml hide: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-xml --&gt;

    &lt;toolchains xmlns=&quot;http://maven.apache.org/TOOLCHAINS/1.1.0&quot; xmlns:xsi=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance&quot;
     xsi:schemaLocation=&quot;http://maven.apache.org/TOOLCHAINS/1.1.0 http://maven.apache.org/xsd/toolchains-1.1.0.xsd&quot;&gt;
     &lt;!-- JDK toolchains --&gt;
     &lt;toolchain&gt;
       &lt;type&gt;jdk&lt;/type&gt;
       &lt;provides&gt;
         &lt;version&gt;1.8&lt;/version&gt;
         &lt;vendor&gt;sun&lt;/vendor&gt;
       &lt;/provides&gt;
       &lt;configuration&gt;
         &lt;jdkHome&gt;/opt/java8&lt;/jdkHome&gt;
       &lt;/configuration&gt;
     &lt;/toolchain&gt;
     &lt;toolchain&gt;
       &lt;type&gt;jdk&lt;/type&gt;
       &lt;provides&gt;
         &lt;version&gt;1.7&lt;/version&gt;
         &lt;vendor&gt;sun&lt;/vendor&gt;
       &lt;/provides&gt;
       &lt;configuration&gt;
         &lt;jdkHome&gt;/opt/java7&lt;/jdkHome&gt;
       &lt;/configuration&gt;
     &lt;/toolchain&gt;
    &lt;/toolchains&gt;

&lt;!-- end snippet --&gt;

It allows you to define what different JDKs Maven can use to build the project irrespective of the JDK Maven runs with. Sort of like when you define JDK on project level in IDE.


  [1]: https://maven.apache.org/guides/mini/guide-using-toolchains.html

To avoid any impact to your project and to your Environment Variables, you can configure the Maven Compiler Plugin just to the project&#39;s POM, specifying the Source and Target java version 

      &lt;plugins&gt;
        &lt;plugin&gt;
    		&lt;artifactId&gt;maven-compiler-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
    		&lt;version&gt;3.5.1&lt;/version&gt;
    		&lt;configuration&gt;
    			&lt;source&gt;1.7&lt;/source&gt;
    			&lt;target&gt;1.7&lt;/target&gt;
    		&lt;/configuration&gt;
    	&lt;/plugin&gt;
        ...
      &lt;/plugins&gt;

In the POM, you can set the compiler properties, e.g. for 1.8:

    &lt;project&gt;
